>21</td></tr></tbody></table></alternatives><table-wrap-foot><fn id="t004fn001"><p>Note: This table presents the difference in average intensity, between before and after the stimulus was presented to the subjects for the 7 emotions analyzed by the facereader software. The standard deviation is given in Parentheses. The row <italic>Valence</italic> contains the change in average valence from before to after the stimulus was presented to the subjects. Valence is calculated as <italic>Happiness</italic> &#x02212; <italic>max</italic>(<italic>Sadness</italic>, <italic>Anger</italic>, <italic>Scare</italic>, <italic>Disgust</italic>). The column labeled <italic>Difference</italic> gives the average difference in emotional intensity between the <italic>Poverty</italic> and <italic>Neutral</italic> treatments. The significance of <italic>Difference</italic> is evaluated with a one sided t-test.</p></fn><fn id="t004fn002"><p>*p&#x0003c;0.1;</p></fn><fn id="t004fn003"><p>** p&#x0003c;0.05;</p></fn><fn id="t004fn004"><p>***p&#x0003c;0.01.</p></fn></table-wrap-foot></table-wrap></sec></sec></sec>